parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the driver's seat to move unexpectedly, making it difficult or impossible to reach the pedals and steering wheel, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The driver's seat moves independently
the interior lights flash on and off
the seat moves to the "easy exit" position
and the vehicle may stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the electrical system crashes
and the charging system warning light appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel lighting can cause difficulty in reading important vehicle information, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The instrument panel lights are inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power driver's seat can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, making it difficult or impossible for the driver to reach the pedals, which can lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The seat moves back or forward on its own
the seat reclines or adjusts without input
the interior lights illuminate or flash
the seat moves to the "easy exit" position
the driver is unable to reach the pedals
the seat moves suddenly and without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle hesitates to switch gears
the vehicle jerks violently when shifting gears
the vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shut-off of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine stalls or shuts off when stopping at a red light
the engine stalls or shuts off when letting off the gas pedal
the vehicle jerks or lurches when restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions in the electronic brain (computer box) can cause a range of problems, including transmission issues, engine stalling, and erratic behavior, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's computer system malfunctions
the transmission shifts erratically
the engine stalls or shuts off
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle's warning lights and indicators illuminate incorrectly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Axle Seal Failure and Oil Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seal can cause oil leakage, leading to premature wear on the axle and potentially causing accidents due to loss of control.
symptoms: Metal scratching noise from the vehicle
oil leakage from the rear axle
premature wear on the axle.
